locality: Vicinity of village of Rizui (Tibetan name = Riza); in saddle and on adjacent N- to NE-facing slopes above village (matsutake harvest site); steep rocky S- to W-facing slopes along trail above village, scrub vegetation dominated by low oaks 1.0-2.5 m tall; wandlike shrubs climbing through other shrubs; corollas light purple
Relatively moist scrub-shrub slope with small Cupressus just past big poplar on trail to Minyong Glacier, below trail. Grazing and cutting evident.
